body_text:
I've tested ubuntu 18.04 too.
$ sudo apt-get install libjpeg-turbo8 libjpeg-turbo8-dev \
zlib1g zlib1g-dev libsnappy1v5 \
libsnappy-dev libre2-4 libre2-dev
$ bazel build --action_env \
TF_SYSTEM_LIBS="com_googlesource_code_re2,jpeg,snappy,zlib_archive" \
//tensorflow:libtensorflow_framework.so \
//tensorflow:libtensorflow.so \
//tensorflow:libtensorflow_cc.so \
//tensorflow/tools/pip_package:build_pip_package

I'm sure unbundling more would work, but those are the ones I've tested.

body:
I've tested ubuntu 18.04 too.
```
$ sudo apt-get install libjpeg-turbo8 libjpeg-turbo8-dev \
zlib1g zlib1g-dev libsnappy1v5 \
libsnappy-dev libre2-4 libre2-dev
$ bazel build --action_env \
TF_SYSTEM_LIBS="com_googlesource_code_re2,jpeg,snappy,zlib_archive" \
//tensorflow:libtensorflow_framework.so \
//tensorflow:libtensorflow.so \
//tensorflow:libtensorflow_cc.so \
//tensorflow/tools/pip_package:build_pip_package
```
I'm sure unbundling more would work, but those are the ones I've tested.
